    "d-notes": {
      "type": "elementRichText",
      "content": "### Director's Notes\n\nI came to this project trying to make a film about water policy. What I found was something harder to name: a family of people whose sense of time is tied to a river's rhythm, and who are now watching that rhythm break apart in slow motion.\n\nI stopped trying to explain the problem. Instead I tried to stay close to what it feels like to live inside it.",
      "level": 4,
      "align": "left",
      "width": "100%",
      "height": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "fade",
        "viewport": { "amount": 0.2 },
        "entranceMotion": { "transition": { "duration": 0.5, "delay": 0 } }
      }
    },
    "d-structure": {
      "type": "elementRichText",
      "content": "### Film Structure\n\n**I. First Light** — 0:00–9:40\nRiver at dawn, daily preparation\n\n**II. Low Season** — 9:40–19:10\nThe changed landscape, family tension\n\n**III. Waiting** — 19:10–28:30\nSilence, memory, the archive\n\n**IV. Downstream** — 28:30–38:00\nFuture conditional; what remains",
      "level": 4,
      "align": "left",
      "width": "100%",
      "height": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "fade",
        "viewport": { "amount": 0.2 },
        "entranceMotion": { "transition": { "duration": 0.5, "delay": 0.08 } }
      }
    },
    "d-craft": {
      "type": "elementRichText",
      "content": "### Craft\n\n**Camera** ARRI Alexa 35, anamorphic glass\n\n**Aspect ratio** 2.39:1\n\n**Format** 4K DCP, 4K DCI\n\n**Sound** Field recorded, no score\n\n**Grade** Dominique Remy\n\n**Runtime** 38 min\n\n**Language** Portuguese, with subtitles",
      "level": 5,
      "align": "left",
      "width": "100%",
      "height": "hug",
      "wordWrap": true,
      "motionTiming": {
        "entrancePreset": "fade",
        "viewport": { "amount": 0.2 },
        "entranceMotion": { "transition": { "duration": 0.5, "delay": 0.16 } }
      }
    }
  }
